12/05/2010
MOGADISHU, Somalia -- Somali pirates seized a Bulgarian-flagged ship in the Gulf of Aden on Tuesday (May 11th), the EU's naval force for the area announced. The Panega, with 15 Bulgarian crew members aboard, was en route from the Red Sea to India or Pakistan. This is the first such hijacking of a Bulgarian-flagged ship. 
On Wednesday, Athens announced that Somali pirates have seized a Greek vessel with at least 24 people onboard, including two Greek citizens and some Filipinos. The vessel, sailing under the Liberian flag, was transporting iron from Ukraine to China. (Vima, AFP, Reuters - 12/05/10; AFP, bTV, Focus - 11/05/10)
